SIMPLE: wield
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wield
<hw>Wield</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Wielded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Wielding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>welden</ets> to
govern, to have power over, to possess, AS. <ets>geweldan</ets>,
<ets>gewyldan</ets>, from <ets>wealdan</ets>; akin to OS.
<ets>waldan</ets>, OFries. <ets>walda</ets>, G. <ets>walten</ets>, OHG.
<ets>waltan</ets>, Icel. <ets>valda</ets>, Sw. <ets>v⟦aring⟧lla</ets> to
occasion, to cause, Dan. <ets>volde</ets>, Goth. <ets>waldan</ets> to
govern, rule, L. <ets>valere</ets> to be strong. Cf. <er>Herald</er>,
<er>Valiant</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To govern; to rule; to keep, or have in charge;
also, to possess.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When a strong armed man keepeth his house, all things that he
<qex>wieldeth</qex> ben in peace.</q> <rj><qau>Wyclif (Luke xi.
21).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Wile [ne will] ye <qex>wield</qex> gold neither silver ne money in
your girdles.</q> <rj><qau>Wyclif (Matt. x. 9.)</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To direct or regulate by influence or authority; to
manage; to control; to sway.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The famous orators . . . whose resistless eloquence⟦br⟧
<qex>Wielded</qex> at will that fierce democraty.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her newborn power was <qex>wielded</qex> from the first by
unprincipled and ambitions men.</q> <rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To use with full command or power, as a thing not
too heavy for the holder; to manage; to handle; hence, to use or employ;
<as>as, to <ex>wield</ex> a sword; to <ex>wield</ex> the
scepter</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Base Hungarian wight! wilt thou the spigot <qex>wield</qex>!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Part <qex>wield</qex> their arms, part curb the foaming steed.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nothing but the influence of a civilized power could induce a
savage to <qex>wield</qex> a spade.</q> <rj><qau>S. S.
Smith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To wield the scepter</b></col>, <cd>to govern with
supreme command.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wieldable</ent>⟦br⟧
